We wanted to make the tracking plugin export convenient for users and ask whether they want to overwrite existing files, by introducing the following lines in [DataExportGui](https://github.com/ilastik/ilastik/blob/2fb916c5424d7bb652f00f5a31d2d86fca7c10a2/ilastik/applets/dataExport/dataExportGui.py#L396-L402)

```py
if self.parentApplet.postprocessCanCheckForExistingFiles():
    exportStatus = self.parentApplet.post_process_lane_export(lane_index, checkOverwriteFiles=True)
    if exportStatus == False:
        if self.showOverwriteQuestion():
            self.parentApplet.post_process_lane_export(lane_index, checkOverwriteFiles=False)
else:
    self.parentApplet.post_process_lane_export(lane_index)
```

Where `showOverwriteQuestion` pops up a message box to the user asking if files should be overwritten, and should continue accordingly.
But because `showOverwriteQuestion` is `@threadRouted`, **it doesn't return anything**.

@stuarteberg @akreshuk is there an elegant way to get the *answer* to a message box basically by something like a `blocking thread routed` call?

Right now, the only way to get files output from the plugin if they are already there from a previous run is if you delete them manually. If there is no straightforward solution then I'll remove that check for existing files completely for this new binary.

@ukoethe is just building the new Windows binary and we noticed that the `Tracking with Learning` workflow does not show up due to an `ImportError: no module named hytra`.
I assume that this is because the new progress bar imports hytra without any checks,
 and doesn't have fallback behaviour for the non-hytra case, but there might be even more cases where it breaks (see e.g. https://github.com/ilastik/ilastik/blob/289c7f92044e8e4e931b6705e7ab64779fdf948b/ilastik/applets/tracking/structured/structuredTrackingGui.py#L23-L23)

@ilastikdev: could you please make sure that Structured Learning (with or without ProgressBar, whatever is easier) works without hytra by moving the `hytra` folder out of `site-packages`, but while having `pgmlink` available?
